  "caption": "India's 3D printing market just crossed $860 million.\n\nBy 2034, it will be worth over $5 billion.\n\nThat is a 20%+ growth rate, year after year, for the next decade.\n\nWhat is fueling this? Healthcare (custom implants, surgical guides), aerospace (lightweight components), automotive (rapid prototyping), and electronics (functional testing).\n\nThe shift is clear: 3D printing in India is moving from \"nice to have\" prototyping tool to \"must have\" production technology.\n\nAt Cu Circuits, we are watching this closely. PCB fabrication and 3D printing are converging. The engineers who master both will build the next generation of Indian hardware products.\n\nAre you using 3D printing in your product development workflow? Tell us how.\n\n#3DPrinting #AdditiveManufacturing #MakeInIndia #IndiaManufacturing #3DPrintingIndia #CuCircuits #FutureOfManufacturing",
